{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"fields":{"description":"Run the discriminates_novelty eval LIVE against the plan-review novelty scorer (prompt src/rebar/llm/reviewers/plan_review_novelty.md) and record the result: post-flip field data shows 33 remediation-eligible reviews produced ZERO novelty drops, which is consistent either with a healthy precision-first quadrant (novel findings rarely both score >= 0.7 novelty AND < 0.4 priority) or with a silently failing scorer (the fail-safe returns zero drops on error). This task determines which, with evidence, and files the follow-up. NOTE: `rebar prompt eval plan-review-novelty` is OFFLINE spec validation only (no model calls, no per-case verdicts - src/rebar/_cli/_llm_eval_commands.py); the live run requires the `nava-rebar[eval]` extra + ANTHROPIC_API_KEY and goes through the live eval runner (`run_eval()` in src/rebar/llm/evals/eval.py, as invoked by the eval CI workflow).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] The offline spec check passes first: `rebar prompt eval plan-review-novelty` reports the spec valid (gate, scorers, gold-set size). Oracle: command exits 0; output recorded in a ticket comment.\n- [ ] The LIVE eval runs to completion from the repo venv with the `[eval]` extra installed, via the live runner path (`run_eval()` / the eval CI invocation for the plan-review-novelty spec), with the exact invocation and the full per-case score/verdict summary recorded as a comment on this ticket. [operator-attested] The comment includes the exact command or runner call, per-case results, and the run timestamp.\n- [ ] The 33 eligible-but-zero-drop reviews are re-examined against the eval outcome: a one-paragraph conclusion comment states whether the scorer discriminates (and drops were correctly withheld) or the scorer is defective. [operator-attested] The conclusion comment cites at least two concrete sidecar examples by ticket id.\n- [ ] If the scorer is defective, a bug ticket is created and linked discovered_from this task; if healthy, this ticket's conclusion says so and no bug is filed. Oracle: `rebar deps <this-id>` shows the discovered_from link in the defective case."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1784093152968023001,"uuid":"3702ce29-5716-4c26-9e8c-303f66d7a7e4"}